<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-089-123 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 142 841</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computer Design  August 1991 v30 n11 p46(3).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>VHDL poised to overtake Verilog as support grows. (TechnologyDirections: CAE/CAD Tools)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Tuck, Barbara.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>The Verilog hardware description language continues to be favoredover VHDL as the lack of tools and models, difficulties with toolinteroperability and lack of verification compliance hinderacceptance of VHDL.andP;  VHDL International was founded in the earlysummer of 1991 by a group of leading electronic design automation(EDA) and application-specific integrated circuit (ASIC) vendorsto promote VHDL as the standard for electronic system design anddescription.andP;  Among VHDL International's founding members areCompass Design Automation, LSI Logic, Logic Automation, MentorGraphics, Synopsys, VLSI Technology, Valid Logic Systems, VantageAnalysis Systems and Viewlogic Systems.andP;  Open VerilogInternational (OVI) was established after Cadence Design Systemsopened Verilog to the public domain; OVI is oriented more towardusers than VHDL International.andP;  VHDL product development byseveral vendors is described.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Hardware Description LanguagesStandardsComparisonVery High Speed Integrated CircuitsCircuit DesignComputer-Aided DesignSoftware PackagesApplication-Specific Integrated CircuitsElectronic Design Automation.andO;Feature:   illustrationgraph.andO;Caption:   Use of Verilog and VHDL: 1989-96. (graph)andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>